For the record. I hired Floppy to work for the foundation on a two month period to start our mining team in April. I hired him because he was a good miner and it helped us understand the network. We fired him because he was *too* good and it caused conflicts of interest because he continued to personally mine. 

Unbeknownst to us he had been dominating the network since January, and continues to since we let him go. The other reality is that we know that his code was not exploitative. Instead highly optimized, employing many optimization on top of his miners akin to what openai has done, i.e. using smaller models to respond quickly to responses in lieu of a timeout, and scaling massively. 

@floppyfish [τ, σ/χ) came forward to tell us that he had monopolized the network **because** he was involved in the foundation. We were privy to so much priceless information because he came forward, and was the major instigator of the June improvements which helped us tremendously and cost him huge portions of his own UIDs. For this reason, and because I understood what had been done, I have always stood for what I considered the truth that they were not cheating. I have yet to talk with anyone who can explain otherwise.

If you desire equal outcome regardless of talent, skill, and hard work. This is not the place for you. Bittensor is built on the concepts of markets, and markets almost always tend to be Pareto. Thus I will always defend those who innovate. It is the engine behind Bittensor which creates us all wealth and helps us achieve our mission.

However I recognize that this has been a very confusing situation for many people. I understand the anger at the lack of transparency. I am here speaking towards that ideal even though I understand this will leave myself open to attack.

BitTensor is a machine learning inference protocol built on Substrate and launched in November 2021. BitTensor aims to harness the power of multiple models to continually iterate and produce better artificial intelligence. The network draws inspiration from Bitcoin, with a 21 million supply of its native currency TAO and a four year halving cycle. Rather than use PoW to generate the correct nonce and earn a block reward, BitTensor harnesses compute from miners in order run inference requests and train better models. As Bitcoin is currently the world’s largest super-computer, 500x larger than the next biggest, BitTensor hopes to provide substantial decentralized compute in order to advance the training of models. 

BitTensor relies on a Mixture of Experts model to collectively improve all models running on the network. The inference process goes like this: (1) An user submits an inference request to the network (2) a validator receives that request and relays it to the network’s miners to run their machine learning models (3) miners run the inference request and produce two outputs - the inference and the weights of their model used to run the inference (4) the inference output is ranked by validators, with the most accurate output receiving the largest reward of TAO (5) lower ranked models can then use the outputs of the higher ranked models in order to train their own model, improving the overall intelligence of the network. 

The blockchain serves three primary purposes for BitTensor: 

1. Tokenomics incentivize miners to contribute compute and models for TAO rewards and validators to secure the network. 
2. Validators submit their rankings to the chain to ensure consensus on the best models. 
3. Miners submit the weights of their models to the chain, creating a transparent means for other miners to update their weights using the model’s of other miners.
